<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-098-446  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 098 446.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Feb 1990 v7 n2 p180(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Adobe Type Manager 1.0: font optimizing utility. (Software Review)(Adobe Systems Adobe Type Manager) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Camus, Luis; Fenton, Erfert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Adobe Systems' $99 Adobe Type Manager (ATM) is a utility forcreating high-quality screen fonts that closely match theirprinted versions.andP;  ATM requires installation of only one screenfont size per typeface on the disk; information in the printerfont is then used to scale the screen font to virtually any sizewithin the 72-dots-per-inch limitation of the Macintosh display.andO;With ATM's high-quality fonts it is possible to print attractivetext on QuickDraw printers.andP;  Any of Adobe's downloadablePostscript fonts and fonts from vendors with Adobe's Type 1 fontformat will work with ATM.andP;  ATM's performance is rated asimpressive regardless of a few problems.andP;  It takes ATM a number ofseconds to scale a block of text and when using Microsoft Word 4.0the letter spacing of the screen display does not always match theprinted output.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adobe Systems Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    ADBE.andO;Product:   Type Manager (Printer software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationOptimizationFontsUtility ProgramsSoftware Packages.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>